---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Challenges Solved</h1>
      <p>The hardest problems I've tackled professionally — and how I approached them.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Turning Around an Underperforming Branch</h2>
        <p class="experience-meta">Enterprise Mobility | 2024</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="grid grid-2">
        <div>
          <h3>The Challenge</h3>
          <p>As a first-term Branch Manager, I inherited a team that was underperforming on key metrics. Profit was flat, employee engagement was low, and customer service rankings were middling. I had 90 days to turn it around.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div>
          <h3>The Approach</h3>
          <p>I focused on three levers: developing my team through 1:1 coaching and clear accountability, controlling costs without cutting service quality, and executing with key accounts to drive revenue. I promoted internally when possible and set clear performance expectations.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div style="margin-top: var(--space-md);">
        <h3>The Results</h3>
        <div class="grid grid-3">
          <div class="card">
            <h3>44%</h3>
            <p>Year-over-year profit increase in my first term</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3>5</h3>
            <p>Employee promotions achieved for my direct reports</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3>6th</h3>
            <p>Place out of 48 branches for customer service</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  
  <section style="background: var(--color-accent-light);">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Getting Surgeons to Adopt New Technology</h2>
        <p class="experience-meta">Arthrex & Medtronic | 2022–Present</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="grid grid-2">
        <div>
          <h3>The Challenge</h3>
          <p>Surgeons are busy, risk-averse, and loyal to proven techniques. Getting them to adopt new orthopedic products or robotic platforms requires building trust, demonstrating clear value, and fitting into their established workflows without adding friction.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div>
          <h3>The Approach</h3>
          <p>At Arthrex, I built relationships with hospital buyers across multiple facilities, getting access for new product sales. At Medtronic, I became certified in the Hugo RAS platform and focused on running smooth cases that demonstrated the technology's value in real surgical settings.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div style="margin-top: var(--space-md);">
        <h3>The Results</h3>
        <div class="grid grid-3">
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Relationships</h3>
            <p>Built key relationships with hospital buyers across southern St. Louis area</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Certification</h3>
            <p>Successfully certified in Medtronic Hugo RAS platform</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Feedback</h3>
            <p>Consistently positive surgeon feedback on case execution</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Scaling Team Performance</h2>
        <p class="experience-meta">Enterprise Mobility | 2024–Present</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="grid grid-2">
        <div>
          <h3>The Challenge</h3>
          <p>Building a high-performing team isn't just about hiring the right people — it's about developing them. I needed to create a culture where people wanted to stay, grow, and excel, while also holding them accountable to high standards.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div>
          <h3>The Approach</h3>
          <p>I implemented structured 1:1s, clear performance metrics, and promotion pathways. I focused on identifying high-potential employees early and giving them stretch opportunities. When someone wasn't performing, I addressed it directly but fairly.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div style="margin-top: var(--space-md);">
        <h3>The Results</h3>
        <div class="grid grid-3">
          <div class="card">
            <h3>5 Promotions</h3>
            <p>Team members promoted under my management</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Top 5</h3>
            <p>Branch finishes among 50 locations</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Retention</h3>
            <p>Built a stable team with low turnover</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  
  <section class="biggest-challenge">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>The Biggest Challenge of My Career</h2>
        <p class="experience-meta">OpenClaw | 2024–Present</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="grid grid-2">
        <div>
          <h3>The Challenge</h3>
          <p>Developing OpenClaw has been the most complex and rewarding challenge of my career. Building an AI agent platform from the ground up required me to dive deep into uncharted territory — learning how to architect agent systems, evaluating LLMs, and creating something that genuinely creates value for users.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div>
          <h3>The Work Involved</h3>
          <p>This challenge pushed me to develop agents from scratch, experiment with multiple LLMs to find the right fit, research emerging tech markets, design file-based structures for agent memory, master prompt engineering, implement sub-agent workflows, identify real-world use cases, and most importantly — act EARLY to leverage AI before the market saturates.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div style="margin-top: var(--space-md);">
        <h3>Why It Matters</h3>
        <p>OpenClaw represents my belief that AI should be accessible and practical. By building this platform, I'm not just learning about technology — I'm creating a tool that can help small businesses and individuals harness the power of AI agents to solve real problems and create value.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
